    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Invisible Matthau</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Letter from Paul Kunino Lynch pays tribute to actor Walter Matthau, who recently died</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Walter Matthau, 79, Rumpled Star and Comic Icon, Dies'' (obituary, July 2):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Walter Matthau, 79, Rumpled Star and Comic Icon, Dies'' (obituary, July 2):</p>
        <p>While still living in Manhattan at the end of the 1960's, Walter Matthau once asserted that he was such a good actor he could make himself invisible while taking his daily walks. I worked nearby, and often saw many people recognize him as he walked down Broadway, but he was held in such universal affection that nobody bothered him.</p>
        <p>PAUL KUNINO LYNCH  Kings Cross, Australia, July 2, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
